        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 20 at 4:01PM EDT by NWS Columbia SC</headline>
        <description>At 401 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Rivers Bridge State Park, or 13 miles south of Bamberg, moving
southeast at 20 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph and pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor damage to outdoor objects is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Barnwell, Bamberg, Denmark, Rivers Bridge State Park, Ehrhardt,
Hilda, Olar, Kline, Govan, and Bamberg County Airport.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
